1. cs.AR (Augmented Reality): The paper discusses the acceleration of deep learning models for mobile applications, which can be used in augmented reality applications. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks for object recognition and semantic segmentation, which are key topics in computer vision. 
3. cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper discusses the use of low-cost, low-power FPGA devices for deep learning acceleration, which is relevant to the field of embedded systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the development of an analytical model for performance estimation of the accelerator, which is relevant to the field of systems and control. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of deep learning models and convolutional neural networks, which are key topics in the field of neural and evolutionary computing.
